msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.82:0.2"
msgid "8. Gilānavagga "
msgstr "8. Sick "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 82. Lokapañhāsutta → lokasuttaṃ (bj) | loko (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.82:0.3"
msgid "82. Lokapañhāsutta "
msgstr "82. A Question On the World "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.82:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.82:2.1"
msgid "“‘Loko, loko’ti, bhante, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of this thing called ‘the world’. "

msgctxt "sn35.82:2.2"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, lokoti vuccatī”ti? "
msgstr "How is the world defined?” "

# NOTE: Using “wear away” we retain something of the pun. Also at AN 3.132 this is clearly the meaning, not “disintegrates”.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.82:2.3"
msgid "“‘Lujjatī’ti kho, bhikkhu, tasmā lokoti vuccati. "
msgstr "“It wears away, mendicant, that’s why it’s called ‘the world’. "

msgctxt "sn35.82:2.4"
msgid "Kiñca lujjati? "
msgstr "And what is wearing away? "

msgctxt "sn35.82:2.5"
msgid "Cakkhu kho, bhikkhu, lujjati. "
msgstr "The eye is wearing away. "

msgctxt "sn35.82:2.6"
msgid "Rūpā lujjanti, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ lujjati, cakkhusamphasso lujjati, yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi lujjati … pe … "
msgstr "Sights … eye consciousness … eye contact is wearing away. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact is also wearing away. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.82:2.7"
msgid "jivhā lujjati … pe … "
msgstr "The ear … nose … tongue … body … "

msgctxt "sn35.82:2.8"
msgid "mano lujjati, dhammā lujjanti, manoviññāṇaṃ lujjati, manosamphasso lujjati, yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi lujjati. "
msgstr "The mind … thoughts … mind consciousness … mind contact is wearing away. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact is also wearing away. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.82:2.9"
msgid "Lujjatīti kho, bhikkhu, tasmā lokoti vuccatī”ti. "
msgstr "It wears away, mendicant, that’s why it’s called ‘the world’.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.82:2.10"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

